    <section class="band band-slim">
      <div class="container">
        <ul class="value-strip">
          <li>
            <a class="value-card" href="/product#map-the-architecture">
              <h3>Map the architecture</h3>
              <p>Expand package hierarchies inline, apply metric heatmaps, filter by coupling strength, and switch to the dependency matrix from a single live model inside the IDE.</p>
              <span class="value-cue">Explore structure</span>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a class="value-card" href="/product#diagnose-structural-problems">
              <h3>Diagnose structural problems</h3>
              <p>Cycles, boundary erosion, and coupling imbalances surfaced at the package level. Accepted exceptions stay visible in the structural graph so governed decisions never hide real problems.</p>
              <span class="value-cue">Find structural problems</span>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a class="value-card" href="/product#prioritize-what-to-fix">
              <h3>Prioritize what to fix</h3>
              <p>Fan-in, fan-out, instability, and abstractness are computed per package and connected to the visual context where they matter. Click any package to see its full metric profile.</p>
              <span class="value-cue">Prioritize refactoring work</span>
            </a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="band band-alt">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header"><span class="section-number">Lenses</span><h2>One architecture model. Five ways to inspect it.</h2></div>
        <p class="section-intro">AtlasArc is not a graph with charts bolted on. It builds a single shared architecture model and lets you look at it five different ways without rerunning analysis each time you switch views.</p>
        <ul class="lens-grid">
          <li class="lens-card">
            <a class="lens-card-link" href="/product/features#explore-structure">
              <span class="lens-type">Structural</span>
              <h3>Topology</h3>
              <p>Understand how the architecture is connected. Explore inline expansion to reveal or collapse detail without losing context.</p>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li class="lens-card">
            <a class="lens-card-link" href="/product/features#explore-structure">
              <span class="lens-type">Relational</span>
              <h3>Matrix</h3>
              <p>Inspect exact dependency relationships. Spot coupling patterns, cycles, and boundary traffic at a glance.</p>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li class="lens-card">
            <a class="lens-card-link" href="/product/features#explore-structure">
              <span class="lens-type">Hierarchical</span>
              <h3>Composition</h3>
              <p>Explore the architecture by area and mass. Switch between treemap, sunburst, and circle pack without reloading the model.</p>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li class="lens-card">
            <a class="lens-card-link" href="/product/features#prioritize-refactoring-work">
              <span class="lens-type">Metric-space</span>
              <h3>Subsystems</h3>
              <p>Plot subsystems in abstract metric space. Find the stable cores and the risky periphery of your codebase.</p>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li class="lens-card">
            <a class="lens-card-link" href="/product/features#prioritize-refactoring-work">
              <span class="lens-type">Metric-space</span>
              <h3>Hotspots</h3>
              <p>Find the packages absorbing the most change pressure, coupling, and complexity; use Galaxy when the map gets dense.</p>
            </a>
          </li>
        </ul>
